===Etymology===
Recorded since 1656; from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημισμός|tr=euphēmismos}}, from {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημίζω|tr=euphēmizō}}, from {{term|lang=grc|εὔφημος|tr=euphēmos||uttering sound of good omen, abstaining from inauspicious words}}, from {{term|εὖ|sc=polytonic|tr=eu||well}} + {{term|lang=grc|φήμη|tr=phēmē||a voice, a prophetic voice, rumor, talk}}, from {{term|lang=grc|φάναι|tr=phanai||to speak, say}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|yoo͞'fə-mĭz"(ə)m}}, {{IPA|/ˈjuː.fəˌmɪ.z(ə)m/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"ju:f@%mIz(@)m/}}

